args.file_text:
Score: 0.7
Reasoning: The core approach (building chains x, x^2, x^4, ...) is largely correct and will handle most cases, but the special-case handling for 1 is incorrect: it computes 2*(freq[1]//2)+1 which can exceed the available count when freq[1] is even. This causes wrong (and even impossible) answers for many inputs containing multiple 1s, so the solution will fail a non-trivial portion of tests.
